description.narrative: Education departments' capacity to generate demand for quality education enhanced in Assam, Bihar, Gujarat, Odisha, Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh and West Bengal through planning, implementation of social and behavior change communication (SBCC) strategies. Life skills content, supportive pedagogy developed for 5 million teachers in 10 states to use with adolescents in-school and out-of-school. Career portal launched in five states to assist 790,000 secondary school students (58 percent girls) in making informed educational and occupational choices. School Management Committees (SMCs) capacitated for enhanced community participation in states. Incremental learning modules, materials for community engagement developed for use by SMCs in six states. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
